SEARCH

All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Application
Represents an Application object in the ApplicationManager program.
Application.AppType
Represents the status of an application after state transitions.
AppList
Maintains a ArrayList of Applications with functionality to add and remove an Application from the list, search for an Application, update an Application, and return sublists.
AppManager
Controls the creation and modification of AppLists.
AppManagerGUI
Container for the ApplicationManager that has the menu options for new application files, loading existing files, saving files and quitting.
AppReader
Reads and processes Application records from a text file into an ArrayList of Applications.
AppWriter
Writes a list of Applications to file.
Command
Encapsulates user actions that cause a state transition for an application.
Command.CommandValue
Represents the four possible commands that a user can make.
Command.Resolution
Represents the four possible ways a user can resolve an application.
